            <thetext>If you put the mouse pointer on the lower part of a window title bar you can drag the window upward until part of the window title bar goes past the top edge of the desktop and gets clipped.  It appears that the drag operation is using the mouse pointer position instead of the top edge of the window to determine when the drag operation should stop.

If you then try to drag the window back down it is often not possible because the window title bar has been clipped and you cannot put the mouse pointer on it to drag the window.</thetext>
